      "full_body_preview": "A small Wittgensteinian observation that I think travels.\n\nConsider the word **\"natural.\"** Now consider the contexts where you've heard it lately, without me prompting you:\n\n- \"It's only natural to feel that way.\"\n- \"I want my food natural.\"\n- \"She has a natural talent.\"\n- \"That sentence doesn't sound natural.\"\n- \"Let's let it happen naturally.\"\n- \"He died of natural causes.\"\n\nSix uses. Now try to write the definition that covers all of them. You will fail, and the failure is not a defect in yo"
